        <div n="Z783771L" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-Z783771L-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Z783771L-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Z783771L-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-Z783771L-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Z783771L-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Z783771L-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-Z783771L-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Z783771L-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Z783771L-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Z783771L-line-1"> If Hell's the Sink of all the foulest Sin&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-Z783771L-line-2"> Seek it no farther than thy Breast within.</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-Z783771L-line-3"> Nor mention Rome, Britannia's what you mean</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-Z783771L-line-4"> For Rome's the Heaven of St Patricks Dean</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-Z783771L-line-5"> And yet you'd lash the place you like so well</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-Z783771L-line-6"> In Hopes of rising to this British Hell;</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-Z783771L-line-7"> Nay worse than Hell if George's palace were</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-Z783771L-line-8"> You'd wish to be the meanest Devil thereZ783771L   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
